tspan.tspan: The hands-tracking in VR has its limitations. The
tracking is done with two cameras pointing from
the player's view. If the cameras can't see the hand
or fingers, it can't properly calculate the positions.
To avoid unintended movement, it is better to place
your
hands in front of you
, in an area, visible by
cameras.
Moreover, it is a good idea, to orient your hands in
a way, so your
fingers are visible
to cameras. And
it is important to have good lighting in the space,
you are playing.
The Care Up VR has simple controls with 3 key
components:
Gaze
. All of the user interface elements can be
interacted with by turning the head toward them and
looking until the countdown is finished.
Grip
. To pick up and interact with some objects, you
need to move your hand into the area of the object
and close the fist. To drop - just open the palm.
Pinch
. Some interactions and pick-up actions with
small objects are done similarly to the grip action, by
placing your hand in the area of the object and
pinching together an index finger and thumb.
